  "market_context": "ETH has been in a continuous downtrend approaching the previous day low. Price sweeps the previous day low along with multiple failure swing lows that had been left untaken during the decline, setting up a potential reversal back into the prior range.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping previous day low and multiple failure swings, price produced a bullish closure through the series of down-close candles on the higher timeframe, then retested a change in state of delivery and fair value gap on the 5-minute, allowing a precise 1-minute entry on the open with tight invalidation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the continuous downtrend on the 1-hour timeframe approaching the previous day low.",
    "Noted the sweep of the previous day low together with multiple failure swing lows left along the decline.",
    "Confirmed the higher timeframe reversal via a bullish closure through the down-close candles back inside the prior range.",
    "Dropped to the 5-minute timeframe to look for confirmation: identified a closure through the series of down-close candles into the important level.",
    "Observed a second 5-minute confirmation as price retested the change in state of delivery into a fair value gap, requiring the 0.5 (CE) to be respected.",
    "Because invalidation sat very close to the opening price of the new higher timeframe candle, prepared an entry on the open using the inversion.",
    "Dropped to the 1-minute timeframe and entered on the open with stop on the low, expecting a shallow wick before expansion higher.",
    "Watched the t-spot form on the 1-minute, confirming price would not return below the low."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade worked — price made the anticipated shallow wick then expanded higher as expected.",
  "lessons": "When invalidation forms very close to the open of a new higher timeframe candle (via inversion and CE respect on the 5-minute), entering on the open of the 1-minute provides a tight-stop, high-probability entry. Failure swings stacked above a swept low act as low resistance liquidity targets.",
